<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-72-0089 </DOCNO><TEXT>The introduction of a universal data base system of Rheinbraun in 1977provided the basis for efficient complex application systems covering,e.g., the whole accounting procedure and permitting interdepartmentallinking. Extensive databases provide models of departments, record datawithout redundancy and including their interrelationships, and provideaccess to data which are logically related but stored in different files.The basic functions, concepts and elements of experience in the modellingof company information systems as well as the centralized and decentralizeduse of planning and reporting systems are explained. (MOS).</TEXT></DOC>